 446     """Parse a :class:`~packaging.tags.Tag` instance.
 447 
 448     :param :class:`~packaging.tags.Tag` tag: A tag to parse
 449     :return: A parsed tag with combined markers, supported platform and python version
 450     :rtype: :class:`~ParsedTag`
 451     """
 452     platform_system = None
 453     python_version = None
 454     version = None
 455     marker_str = ""
 456     if tag.platform.startswith("macos"):
 457         platform_system = "Darwin"
 458     elif tag.platform.startswith("manylinux") or tag.platform.startswith("linux"):
 459         platform_system = "Linux"
 460     elif tag.platform.startswith("win32"):
 461         platform_system = "Windows"
 462     if platform_system:
 463         marker_str = 'platform_system == "{}"'.format(platform_system)
 464     if tag.interpreter:
 465         version = tag.interpreter[2:]
 466         py_version_str = ""
 467         if len(version) == 1:
 468             py_version_str = ">={}.0,<{}".format(version, str(int(version) + 1))
 469         elif len(version) > 1 and len(version) <= 3:
 470             # reverse the existing version so we can add 1 to the first element
 471             # and re-reverse, generating the new version, e.g. [3, 2, 8] =>
 472             # [8, 2, 3] => [9, 2, 3] => [3, 2, 9]
 473             next_version_list = list(reversed(version[:]))
 474             next_version_list[0] = str(int(next_version_list[0]) + 1)
 475             next_version = ".".join(list(reversed(next_version_list)))
 476             version = ".".join(version)
 477             py_version_str = ">={},<{}".format(version, next_version)
 478         else:
 479             py_version_str = "{0}".format(version)
 480         python_version = marker_from_specifier(py_version_str)
 481     if python_version:
 482         if marker_str:
 483             marker_str = "{0} and {1!s}".format(marker_str, python_version)
 484         else:
 485             marker_str = str(python_version)
 486     return ParsedTag(
 487         marker_string=marker_str,
 488         python_version=version,
 489         platform_system=platform_system,
